Bishop Maurice Crowley of the Kitale Catholic Diocese has lost his mother after a long illness at a London hospital. Nora Crowley, 94, died on Friday. This came barely days after the son was named acting Eldoret Diocese bishop following the death of Cornelius Korir. Read: Pope appoints Kitale Bishop Crowley to act in Eldoret after death of Bishop Korir Crowley will be the apostolic administrator of the diocese until a new bishop is named by Pope Francis. Kiminini MP Chris Wamalwa, chairman of the Catholic MPs
association, said they will
stand with the family during this difficult time.
